Phase 3: Sanity v3 Headless CMS – Implementation Plan
1. Scope and constraints
Replace the current /insights placeholder with a Sanity-powered insights hub.
Keep the existing /insights/semigration-retirement static page as-is (or later migrate it to a Sanity article); the plan focuses on the new dynamic insights index and article route.
FAIS: Centralise FSP 17273 disclaimers in an fspEntity document and inject them via a custom Portable Text block fspDisclosure.
SEO: Target “semigration” and related terms; all article-level SEO via seoMetadata (title/description length checks, canonical, OG image, noIndex).
Studio: Embedded at /studio; Draft Mode + Visual Editing must not run under /studio (use pathname check or route group).
2. File and folder structure
sanity/  schemaTypes/    index.ts              # Export all types + structure    objects/      seoMetadata.ts      # Reusable SEO object    documents/      article.ts          # Article document (body: PT, references seoMetadata, locale-aware slug)      fspEntity.ts        # FSP 17273 license / disclaimer document    blocks/      fspDisclosure.ts    # Custom PT block: reference to fspEntity, render as disclaimer box  lib/    client.ts             # createClient (next-sanity) – projectId, dataset, apiVersion, stega    fetch.ts              # sanityFetch wrapper using React cache() for request deduplication    live.ts               # defineLive(client, serverToken, browserToken) → sanityFetch, SanityLive  env.ts                  # Validation for NEXT_PUBLIC_SANITY_* and SANITY_VIEWER_TOKEN (optional)sanity.config.ts          # defineConfig: project, dataset, schema, plugins (presentationTool, etc.)app/  studio/    [[...tool]]/      page.tsx            # Embedded Sanity Studio (dynamic route)  api/    draft-mode/      enable/        route.ts          # defineEnableDraftMode({ client with token })  (main)/                 # Or use pathname in root layout to exclude /studio    layout.tsx            # Existing root layout; add conditional SanityLive + VisualEditing (see 5)  insights/    page.tsx              # Insights index: list articles (sanityFetch + GROQ), link to [slug]    [slug]/      page.tsx            # Dynamic article page: sanityFetch by slug, generateMetadata, PT + custom fspDisclosurecomponents/  DisableDraftMode.tsx    # Optional: button to disable draft mode when not in Presentation tool  portable-text/    ArticlePortableText.tsx  # PortableText with custom types.fspDisclosure → FspDisclosureBlock    FspDisclosureBlock.tsx   # Renders referenced fspEntity as styled disclaimer box
Sanity Studio: Served at /studio via app/studio/[[...tool]]/page.tsx (or [[...index]] per next-sanity embedding docs).
Draft Mode: Enabled by GET /api/draft-mode/enable (and optionally disabled via server action + DisableDraftMode).
Visual Editing: VisualEditing and SanityLive only when draft mode is on and pathname is not /studio (or under a studio route). Use a small client wrapper that uses usePathname() and only then renders SanityLive + (when draft) VisualEditing, so the studio layout never gets them.
3. Sanity Studio and schema architecture
3.1 Paths and entrypoint
Config: sanity.config.ts at project root (or under sanity/ and imported from root). Plugins: structureTool, presentationTool (with previewUrl.previewMode.enable: "/api/draft-mode/enable"), and any locale plugin if used.
Schema entry: sanity/schemaTypes/index.ts exports the schema and optionally structure for the desk.
3.2 Reusable seoMetadata object (sanity/schemaTypes/objects/seoMetadata.ts)
Fields:
metaTitle (string) – Rule: Rule.max(65).warning('Keep under 65 characters for SEO')
metaDescription (string) – Rule: Rule.max(160).warning('Keep under 160 characters')
canonicalUrl (string, optional) – URL
openGraphImage (image, optional) – Sanity image type
noIndex (boolean, default false) – noindex when true
Used as an embedded object in article (and optionally other documents later).
3.3 Document: article (sanity/schemaTypes/documents/article.ts)
Fields:
title (string, required)
slug (slug, required) – Document-level localization: same document can have EN vs AF slug via plugin or a locale field that affects slug uniqueness (e.g. slug unique per locale). Implementation option A: use @sanity/document-internationalization and language-specific documents with their own slugs. Option B: single document with locale (e.g. en | af) and slug validated unique per locale.
locale (string, optional) – e.g. en, af for separate EN/AF SEO slugs and generateMetadata/canonical.
publishedAt (datetime, optional)
excerpt (text, optional) – for cards and meta description fallback
body (array, block content) – Portable Text; may include the custom block fspDisclosure.
seo (object) – embedded seoMetadata.
Document-level localization: Plan is to support separate English and Afrikaans SEO slugs (e.g. one document per language or one doc with locale + slug). Schema will expose slug.current and locale so GROQ can resolve by slug and optionally locale.
3.4 Document: fspEntity (sanity/schemaTypes/documents/fspEntity.ts)
Purpose: Single source of truth for FSP 17273 (and any other FSP) license and legal disclaimer text.
Fields (example):
name (string) – e.g. "AS Brokers CC"
fspNumber (string) – e.g. "17273"
disclaimerText (text or block content) – the legal disclaimer to show in articles.
Usage: Referenced by the custom block fspDisclosure so editors pick an FSP entity and the front end renders it in a compliant disclaimer box.
3.5 Custom Portable Text block: fspDisclosure (sanity/schemaTypes/blocks/fspDisclosure.ts)
Type: Block (custom block type in the PT schema).
Fields:
fspEntity (reference) – to document type fspEntity.
Optional: variant (string) – e.g. "default" | "compact" for styling.
Rendering: In @portabletext/react, a custom component for type fspDisclosure will resolve the reference, read fspEntity.disclaimerText (and name/number), and render a styled disclaimer box at the bottom of the article (or wherever the block is placed).
4. Data fetching and memoization
4.1 Sanity client (sanity/lib/client.ts)
createClient from next-sanity with:
projectId, dataset, apiVersion (e.g. "2024-12-01"),
useCdn: true for production,
stega: { studioUrl } for Visual Editing,
no token on the base client (token passed where needed for draft content).
Export client.
4.2 Request deduplication (sanity/lib/fetch.ts)
React cache(): Next.js 15 does not cache fetch by default. To ensure one network request when both generateMetadata and the default Page component request the same article:
Either use the sanityFetch returned by defineLive (if it is already memoized per request), or
Wrap the GROQ fetch in cache() and call that from both generateMetadata and the page.
Plan: Implement a sanityFetch wrapper that:
Takes a GROQ query and params.
Uses cache() from React so that the same (query, params) in the same request only hits Sanity once.
Calls client.fetch(query, params, options) (or the sanityFetch from defineLive if it accepts a similar signature). If we use defineLive, we will use its sanityFetch everywhere and, if the docs do not guarantee deduplication with generateMetadata, wrap the call in cache() in sanity/lib/fetch.ts and re-export (e.g. cachedSanityFetch).
4.3 Live content (sanity/lib/live.ts)
defineLive from next-sanity/live:
client from sanity/lib/client.ts,
serverToken: process.env.SANITY_VIEWER_TOKEN,
browserToken: same (only used when draft mode is on).
Export sanityFetch and SanityLive from this file.
All article (and insights index) data will be fetched with this sanityFetch so that Draft Mode + Live Content work correctly.
5. Next.js 15 Draft Mode and Visual Editing
5.1 Route: app/api/draft-mode/enable/route.ts
defineEnableDraftMode from next-sanity/draft-mode:
client: client.withConfig({ token: process.env.SANITY_VIEWER_TOKEN }).
Export GET handler so that the Presentation tool can open the app with draft mode enabled.
5.2 Root layout (app/layout.tsx)
Conditional injection (embedded studio safe):
SanityLive – must be present for live updates and draft/published switching, but must not run on the /studio route (to avoid reloads/conflicts).
VisualEditing – only when draft mode is enabled and not on /studio.
Implementation: Add a client component (e.g. SanityVisualEditing.tsx) that:
Uses usePathname() and skips rendering when pathname.startsWith('/studio').
Renders <SanityLive /> always when not on /studio (so that sanityFetch is live).
Renders <VisualEditing /> only when draft mode is enabled (e.g. via a small server-boundary wrapper that passes isDraftMode as prop, or by using a hook/context from next-sanity if available). If next-sanity does not expose draft mode to the client, alternative is to render VisualEditing in the server layout only when draftMode().isEnabled and pathname !== '/studio'; then we need a way to get pathname on the server (e.g. headers or a separate layout for (content) route group that wraps everything except /studio).
Recommended: Use a route group (content) so that:
app/(content)/layout.tsx wraps all non-studio routes and renders SanityLive + conditional VisualEditing (when draft mode is on). Root app/layout.tsx stays minimal (font, globals, AppShell).
app/studio/[[...tool]]/page.tsx is outside (content), so it never gets SanityLive or VisualEditing.
Summary: Either (A) client wrapper that checks pathname and only mounts SanityLive + VisualEditing when pathname is not under /studio, and VisualEditing only when draft mode is true (passed from server), or (B) route group (content) with a server layout that adds SanityLive and VisualEditing (when draft) for all non-studio routes. Plan assumes (B) for clarity: app/(content)/layout.tsx contains the Draft Mode check and renders SanityLive and conditional VisualEditing.
6. GROQ queries
6.1 Insights index (list articles)
Query name (e.g.): insightsList.
GROQ (concept):
*[_type == "article" && defined(slug.current)] | order(publishedAt desc) { _id, title, slug, excerpt, publishedAt, "seo": seo }.
If using locale: add && locale == $locale and pass locale (default "en").
Usage: app/insights/page.tsx uses sanityFetch({ query: insightsList, params: { locale: "en" } }) and renders a list of links to /insights/[slug].
6.2 Single article by slug (for page + metadata)
Query name (e.g.): articleBySlug.
GROQ (concept):
*[_type == "article" && slug.current == $slug][0] { _id, title, slug, excerpt, publishedAt, body, seo }.
If using locale: && slug.current == $slug && locale == $locale.
Usage: Same query used in generateMetadata and in the default export of app/insights/[slug]/page.tsx, with both calls going through the cached sanityFetch so only one request is made per request.
6.3 FSP entity for disclaimer (resolved inside PT or in a separate query)
Option A: In the article query, expand the reference in body so that any fspDisclosure block includes the resolved fspEntity (e.g. body[] { ..., _type == "fspDisclosure" => { ..., "fsp": fspEntity-> } }).
Option B: Resolve fspEntity in the serializer by doing a separate fetch by id when rendering fspDisclosure. Prefer Option A in the main article query so that one GROQ request still suffices and the serializer only renders.
7. The insights route and article page
7.1 app/insights/page.tsx
Data: sanityFetch(insightsList) (with locale if used).
UI: Replace placeholder with a list of articles (title, excerpt, publishedAt, link to /insights/[slug]). Reuse existing layout (e.g. section + Footer). Optional: use generateMetadata for insights index SEO (e.g. from a static or single “Insights” document in Sanity).
7.2 app/insights/[slug]/page.tsx
Params: params: Promise<{ slug: string }> (Next 15).
Data: sanityFetch(articleBySlug, { slug }) with body expanded to resolve fspDisclosure.fspEntity->.
generateMetadata: Same sanityFetch(articleBySlug, { slug }) (via cached wrapper) to derive title, description, openGraph, canonical, robots (if seo.noIndex).
Rendering:
Article title, publishedAt, excerpt.
Portable Text: @portabletext/react with a custom components.types.fspDisclosure that renders FspDisclosureBlock (styled disclaimer box using resolved fspEntity name, FSP number, and disclaimer text). All other block types use default or minimal customisation.
404: If query returns null, notFound().
7.3 Custom serializer: fspDisclosure → disclaimer box
Component: e.g. FspDisclosureBlock.tsx. Receives value (block with fspEntity reference; resolved in GROQ to fsp or similar).
Rendering: A bordered/background box (e.g. bottom of article or inline) with:
FSP name and number (e.g. “AS Brokers CC · FSP 17273”),
Disclaimer text from fspEntity.disclaimerText,
Optional “FAIS compliant” or similar short line.
Styling: Match site (e.g. border-white/10, bg-white/5, small type) so it is clearly a legal disclaimer.
8. Dependencies and env
Packages: next-sanity, @sanity/client (if not bundled by next-sanity), @portabletext/react, sanity (for Studio config and schema). Optional: @sanity/document-internationalization if using document-level localization with the plugin.
Env (app):
NEXT_PUBLIC_SANITY_PROJECT_ID
NEXT_PUBLIC_SANITY_DATASET
NEXT_PUBLIC_SANITY_STUDIO_URL (e.g. http://localhost:3000/studio for embed)
SANITY_VIEWER_TOKEN (Viewer role, for draft content and Presentation tool)
Env (Studio): Same project/dataset; optional SANITY_STUDIO_PREVIEW_ORIGIN for Presentation tool.
9. Summary checklist (for your approval)
Item	Detail
Studio	Embedded at /studio; config in sanity.config.ts; schemas under sanity/schemaTypes/.
seoMetadata	Object: metaTitle (max 65 warning), metaDescription (max 160), canonicalUrl, openGraphImage, noIndex.
article	Document with title, slug, locale (optional), publishedAt, excerpt, body (PT), seo (embedded). Document-level localization for EN/AF slugs.
fspEntity	Document: name, fspNumber, disclaimerText.
fspDisclosure	Custom PT block: reference to fspEntity; serializer renders disclaimer box.
Client	sanity/lib/client.ts with stega; token only where needed.
Fetch	sanity/lib/fetch.ts: cached wrapper so generateMetadata + page share one request.
Live	sanity/lib/live.ts: defineLive → sanityFetch, SanityLive.
Draft	app/api/draft-mode/enable/route.ts: defineEnableDraftMode.
Layout	SanityLive + VisualEditing (when draft) only for non-studio routes (e.g. via (content) layout).
Insights index	app/insights/page.tsx: sanityFetch(insightsList), list articles → /insights/[slug].
Article page	app/insights/[slug]/page.tsx: sanityFetch(articleBySlug), generateMetadata, PT + fspDisclosure serializer.
If you confirm this plan (and any choices like route group vs pathname check, and EN/AF via plugin vs single locale field), the next step is to implement it in code as specified.